'cluster'\",message=\"TrustManager is a singleton, .metadata.name must be 'cluster'\"\n```\n\n### Commands to run (in order)\n\nFrom the repository root:\n\n```bash\nmake manifests\n```\n\nThis single command will:\n1. Run `controller-gen` to regenerate the CRD YAML in `config/crd/bases/` — it will add an `x-kubernetes-validations` entry to the CertManager CRD schema with the CEL rule.\n2. Update the bundle manifest in `bundle/manifests/` with the new validation.\n\n### What the generated CRD change looks like\n\nAfter `make manifests`, the CertManager CRD YAML will gain an `x-kubernetes-validations` block at the top level of the schema (same level as the `openAPIV3Schema` `properties`), like this:\n\n```yaml\n    schema:\n      openAPIV3Schema:\n        description: CertManager is the Schema for the certmanagers API\n        ...\n        x-kubernetes-validations:\n        - message: CertManager is a singleton, .metadata.name must be 'cluster'\n          rule: self.metadata.name == 'cluster'\n```\n\nThis ensures that any attempt to create a `CertManager` resource with `metadata.name` set to anything other than `'cluster'` will be rejected at admission time by the Kubernetes API server's CEL validation.\n\n### No other files need manual changes\n\nThe only file you edit by hand is `certmanager_types.go`. All other affected files (`config/crd/bases/operator.openshift.io_certmanagers.yaml`, `bundle/manifests/cert-manager-operator.clusterserviceversion.yaml`, and the CRD in `bundle/manifests/`) are regenerated automatically by `make manifests`."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":560,"cache_read_input_tokens":44659,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":560,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c62453c8-e16c-4cb8-ac40-4226525deac5","uuid":"7ecb57c2-c4b2-413d-bdf9-07446de0c1bf","timestamp":"2026-07-20T18: